Organization = {IEEE; Tribhuvan Univ, Pulchowk Campus},
Abstract = {The pandemic hit the world, and governments all around the world adopted
   drastic but necessary steps to stop it from spreading may be COVID or
   other versions. It's difficult to ensure that individuals follow these
   important social distance principles in large institutions. An automated
   system is necessary to enable easy tracking of such offenders. As a
   result, this system was designed to identify specific infractions in
   real-time. The proposed system's initial use is to recognize faces of
   people to decide whether they are wearing an approved mask or not. The
   other use is to evaluate whether the social distance is maintained
   between two people in the most efficient manner that is very accurate,
   and easy way possible, requiring the least amount of effort from
   supervisory authorities.},
