   Applicat \& Living Domains; Dortmund Univ Appl Sci \& Arts},
Abstract = {This paper presents the interdisciplinary project aimed at detecting the
   undesired or dangerous behavior of persons in the confined institutions
   such as prisons or wards, based on the video streams provided by the
   CCTV cameras. Currently, there are IT systems working in such areas, but
   their efficiency is limited, forcing the operator to focus his/her
   attention on every image separately. Design of a system for autonomous
   detection of anomalous behaviors - such as fights or passing illegal
   material - based on the input from multiple surveillance cameras would
   allow for providing the decision support module. With the acceptable
   detection accuracy, the solution would help in minimizing the accidents
   and unwanted behavior of monitored inmates. The system should also
   provide the catalogue of predefined dangerous situations, prepared by
   the experts in criminal sciences, including the features useful for
   predicting the specific events.},
