   12-13, 2022},
Organization = {Ctr Smart Soc; Inst Business Management; Coll Comp Sci \& Informat Syst},
Abstract = {To calculate the novel time usage for the crime analysis using K-Nearest
   Neighbor algorithm compared with Random Forest algorithm on Data of
   Crimes. K-Nearest Neighbor with sample size = 247 and Random Forest with
   sample size = 154 with G power (value = 0.8) were calculated many times
   to predict the accuracy percentage for the various crime data. K-Nearest
   Neighbor has significantly done with better accuracy (86.75\%) compared
   to Random Forest (84.53\%) and the statistical significance difference
   (two-tailed) is 0.01 (p!0.05). Based on Independent T-test analysis
   using SPSS statistical software, K-Nearest Neighbor achieved
   significantly better than Random Forest for novel time usage
   calculation.},
