Organization = {PES Inst Technol, Bangalore South Campus; IEEE; IEEE Communicat Soc;
   IEEE Photon Soc; IEEE Robot \& Automat Soc},
Abstract = {In this age of Big Data, the data is broadly distributed all through the
   web which can be utilized for criminal and non criminal exercises. A
   third party with a proper tool can sniff into the communication process
   between the legitimate users. With remarkable development in computer
   technology nowadays, 1-way authentication (e. g. passwords) is no more
   analyzed as secure in the Internet. It has never been less troublesome
   in protecting the system and remote access. 2-way authentication
   guarantees a higher security level than 1-way authentication. This paper
   proposes a highly secured 2-way authentication between client and server
   using Zero Knowledge Protocol (ZKP) in web applications. Additionally,
   our system ensures the data confidentiality and integrity during
   communication process which is very relevant in the present day
   scenario.},
