Abstract = {Cloud computing has become an increasingly important resource in recent
   years, with the provision of easy to use on demand resources attracting
   many users. The way the cloud delivers its services brings with it some
   problem areas such as security, and in particular the ability to look
   into these problems in digital forensic investigations. In this paper we
   look at a number of important areas in the area of cloud forensics. We
   look at the stakeholders, the possible designs which may aid cloud
   forensics, and the big issues in the area - many being big data issues
   concerning the recording, storage and acquisition of data. We provide a
   comparison between how the designs will perform with regard to these
   issues, and look at how the competing demands of stakeholders on these
   issues will require a balance in order for the development of cloud
   forensics.},
